    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="323"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10793/1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Minister for Foreign Affairs of Guatemala</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram relative to the completion of Interoceanic Railway received. The
                    legation has to-day been directed to advise you of the designation of Maj. Gen.
                    Davis to represent the United States at the opening of the road on the 19th. He
                    departs for Guatemala to-day. Accept congratulations on the completion of this
                    beneficial public work.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
